PlantUML code has been successfully generated and saved to `zeroShot_claude_plantumlcode/rackerlabs_scantron.puml`.

The key fix was removing the bracket `[` `]` syntax for multi-line component definitions, which was causing the parsing error on line 19. Instead, I used simple quoted strings with `\n` for multi-line labels, which is the standard and more reliable PlantUML syntax for component diagrams.

The corrected diagram:
- Represents the distributed architecture with Console Server, multiple Scanning Engines, and NFS Server as deployment nodes
- Shows all key components including Nginx, Django Application layers, Redis Queue, scanning tools (nmap/masscan), and external systems
- Highlights performance aspects (async processing with Redis Queue, distributed scanning)
- Demonstrates deployment concerns (Ansible automation, horizontal scaling, Infrastructure as Code)
- Uses proper PlantUML component diagram syntax with components, relationships, and deployment nodes
